1
00:00:01,626 --> 00:00:03,753
<i>Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.</i>

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:07,132
<i>People who have used these drugs</i>

3
00:00:07,215 --> 00:00:10,719
<i>are now estimated</i>
<i>to total two million in Japan.</i>

4
00:00:11,261 --> 00:00:14,347
<i>The number of people arrested</i>
<i>for drug-related offenses</i>

5
00:00:14,931 --> 00:00:17,058
<i>is as many as 14,000 yearly.</i>

6
00:00:18,184 --> 00:00:22,397
I won't tell a soul
that I bought from the Saeki Family!

7
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:24,691
Please, have mercy on me!

8
00:00:28,403 --> 00:00:32,198
<i>This adds damage to property</i>
<i>on top of inflicting bodily injury.</i>

9
00:00:32,282 --> 00:00:33,199
Come on, man!

10
00:00:33,283 --> 00:00:36,161
Cutting my face? Have you gone insane?

11
00:00:36,244 --> 00:00:38,121
Are you fucking mad?

12
00:00:38,204 --> 00:00:41,958
The NCD has Kurosaki, who'll use
any means to make a suspect talk.

13
00:00:42,041 --> 00:00:45,336
<i>His mother</i>
<i>wasn't just a regular meth addict.</i>

14
00:00:46,504 --> 00:00:50,550
<i>She was fed meth and forced</i>
<i>into becoming a sex addict.</i>

15
00:00:51,551 --> 00:00:53,136
It's your fault.

16
00:00:53,219 --> 00:00:55,013
<i>Meth laid waste to his family.</i>

17
00:00:55,638 --> 00:00:58,933
<i>That's why he bears</i>
<i>a deep hatred for drugs.</i>

18
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:00,769
To avenge his mother.

19
00:01:00,852 --> 00:01:03,480
So he's not just an asshole.

20
00:01:04,773 --> 00:01:05,940
What is this?

21
00:01:06,024 --> 00:01:07,233
Hey, wait!

22
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,110
What are you doing?

23
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:10,737
Isn't she a victim?

24
00:01:12,155 --> 00:01:14,282
-Let's go.
-Wait!

25
00:01:14,783 --> 00:01:19,621
I said you would hurt those dear to you
and lose everything if you did drugs.

26
00:01:20,371 --> 00:01:23,249
Please, just come back
to your senses, you idiot!

27
00:01:35,887 --> 00:01:39,599
The urine test detected
cocaine metabolites.

28
00:01:41,726 --> 00:01:42,936
You tested positive.

29
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:55,240
What is your relationship
with Hibiki Kaga?

30
00:01:57,826 --> 00:02:02,372
Kaga forced you into taking cocaine,
and then you couldn't stop.

31
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:04,582
Isn't that so?

32
00:02:09,712 --> 00:02:11,714
Start talking and answer me.

33
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:23,226
She was cooperative with the urine test.

34
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:26,563
She has to be hiding something.

35
00:02:27,313 --> 00:02:29,774
Maybe she likes Kaga
and is covering for him.

36
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:32,986
No, that's not the impression I get.

37
00:02:33,528 --> 00:02:35,196
But there's still something.

38
00:02:37,490 --> 00:02:38,491
Chief.

39
00:02:39,409 --> 00:02:41,369
Let me conduct the questioning.

40
00:02:42,579 --> 00:02:45,707
You know he won't let
anyone else take charge of it.

41
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:49,043
There are things women
can only tell other women.

42
00:02:49,961 --> 00:02:53,256
Especially if a man put her
through a terrible experience.

43
00:02:55,675 --> 00:03:00,597
She may be a drug user,
but she could also be a victim.

44
00:03:01,180 --> 00:03:02,307
Please.

45
00:03:03,725 --> 00:03:08,980
For her, this interrogation could define
her whole life going forward.

46
00:03:14,652 --> 00:03:16,654
Go convince Kurosaki.

47
00:03:18,239 --> 00:03:19,115
Yes, sir.

48
00:03:23,953 --> 00:03:25,288
You sure about that?

49
00:03:26,247 --> 00:03:27,373
Yes.

50
00:03:29,751 --> 00:03:32,253
You two could learn
a thing or two from her.

51
00:04:27,767 --> 00:04:29,560
This room is occupied.

52
00:04:29,644 --> 00:04:31,104
Give me just ten minutes.

53
00:04:31,187 --> 00:04:33,356
-No. Get out.
-Please!

54
00:04:34,565 --> 00:04:36,567
What can a rookie
like you even accomplish?

55
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:43,324
Are those…

56
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:10,393
Hesitation marks?

57
00:05:17,525 --> 00:05:19,110
I was scared…

58
00:05:21,237 --> 00:05:22,363
of dying.

59
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:36,127
I'm glad.

60
00:05:38,087 --> 00:05:39,380
What?

61
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,343
That you weren't bold enough to die.

62
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:53,311
I'm sorry.

63
00:05:54,937 --> 00:05:57,648
If only we had caught Kaga sooner,

64
00:05:58,316 --> 00:06:00,943
you wouldn't have had to go through this.

65
00:06:09,702 --> 00:06:11,120
Just five minutes.

66
00:06:11,662 --> 00:06:13,956
Let me ask what she's going through.

67
00:06:39,232 --> 00:06:41,442
You're saying you did cocaine,

68
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:44,320
so you could forget about Kaga?

69
00:06:46,823 --> 00:06:47,907
Yes.

70
00:06:50,952 --> 00:06:52,161
Over and over,

71
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:58,751
I would see his face.

72
00:07:01,087 --> 00:07:03,297
It wouldn't leave my mind.

73
00:07:05,133 --> 00:07:06,175
Flashbacks.

74
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:12,598
Was this the first time you bought
and did cocaine by yourself?

75
00:07:17,186 --> 00:07:18,646
It was my second time.

76
00:07:22,191 --> 00:07:24,527
When I did it by myself the first time,

77
00:07:26,237 --> 00:07:31,284
I was able to forget about him,
even for just a moment.

78
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:33,619
I see.

79
00:07:34,787 --> 00:07:36,330
It must have been tough.

80
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:40,543
But you know,

81
00:07:41,669 --> 00:07:44,255
even if you use drugs
when times are tough,

82
00:07:45,047 --> 00:07:48,426
it gets worse when the drugs run out,
and you get withdrawal.

83
00:07:49,343 --> 00:07:51,304
Then you turn to drugs again.

84
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:56,642
It makes you unable
to keep on living without cocaine.

85
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:02,315
Listen.

86
00:08:03,816 --> 00:08:07,862
Don't throw away the rest of your life
because of a horrible man like him.

87
00:08:11,449 --> 00:08:14,118
We'll make sure Kaga
pays for what he has done.

88
00:08:15,328 --> 00:08:19,081
We'll do whatever we can
to alleviate your worries.

89
00:08:19,165 --> 00:08:20,791
I promise you!

90
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:33,012
Thank you.

91
00:08:48,611 --> 00:08:50,363
There.

92
00:08:57,078 --> 00:08:59,372
She's a victim! So why--

93
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:01,499
She's no longer a victim
if she buys cocaine herself!

94
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,044
We have a responsibility to arrest her.

95
00:09:05,878 --> 00:09:07,547
You're a dealer.

96
00:09:07,630 --> 00:09:10,550
You should already know
the hell that awaits her.

97
00:09:19,517 --> 00:09:21,727
What's wrong? Not going to eat that?

98
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:25,648
I mean, anyone would get tired
of <i>okonomiyaki </i>two days in a row.

99
00:09:27,942 --> 00:09:28,776
Yum!

100
00:09:30,069 --> 00:09:33,239
Yesterday's were Hiroshima style.
These are Kure City style.

101
00:09:33,322 --> 00:09:36,659
The half-moon look is
the main difference between them.

102
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:39,328
It uses Kure's specialty
thin udon noodles.

103
00:09:40,121 --> 00:09:41,956
Listen, there are several varieties

104
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:45,001
under the umbrella
of Hiroshima's <i>okonomiyaki</i>.

105
00:09:45,084 --> 00:09:48,629
The taste and texture differ
based on the use of soba or udon.

106
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:51,424
That is what defines
Hiroshima's <i>okonomiyaki</i>.

107
00:09:54,594 --> 00:09:56,929
I don't care as long as it tastes good.

108
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:58,556
But come on,

109
00:09:58,639 --> 00:10:02,310
you didn't call me just to lecture me
on Hiroshima's <i>okonomiyaki</i>.

110
00:10:07,315 --> 00:10:11,444
We found out that Nagata's company
is linked to the Saeki Family.

111
00:10:11,527 --> 00:10:14,780
Nagata is the guy
who sold drugs to Kaga, right?

112
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:17,283
He's linked to the yakuza too?

113
00:10:17,366 --> 00:10:20,494
Matsubara, your boss,
also gets cocaine from the Saeki Family.

114
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:21,662
You didn't know that?

115
00:10:21,746 --> 00:10:24,790
No, us underlings weren't told
any details about the route.

116
00:10:26,500 --> 00:10:30,129
That's most likely how
Nagata got his cocaine.

117
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:31,339
Given that,

118
00:10:32,256 --> 00:10:36,427
your job is to make Kurosaki accept
a plan prepared by the police.

119
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:37,803
What?

120
00:10:37,887 --> 00:10:40,097
You know Kurosaki won't listen to me.

121
00:10:40,181 --> 00:10:42,558
This is what you'll suggest to Kurosaki,

122
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:44,560
"Let's get not just Nagata,

123
00:10:44,644 --> 00:10:47,897
but also the organization
that was selling drugs to him.

124
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:50,524
I'll go and investigate
their smuggling routes."

125
00:10:50,608 --> 00:10:53,152
You think Kurosaki would fall for that?

126
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:56,989
If you share the information that Nagata
got his cocaine from the Saeki Family,

127
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,991
Kurosaki will definitely bite.

128
00:10:59,742 --> 00:11:02,995
Why would you let Kurosaki
know that anyway?

129
00:11:03,079 --> 00:11:05,623
Isn't the NCD
a rival organization to the police?

130
00:11:05,706 --> 00:11:08,292
Why not just conduct
your own investigation?

131
00:11:08,376 --> 00:11:10,836
As a trade-off for
the police's great authority,

132
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:15,257
the law binds us tightly and oversees us,
so we can't do aggressive investigations.

133
00:11:15,966 --> 00:11:18,677
On the other hand,
the NCD has special privileges,

134
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,930
such as the right to do sting operations.

135
00:11:21,013 --> 00:11:24,350
That's why we let them gather evidence,

136
00:11:24,433 --> 00:11:28,396
and you'll leak it to us by sticking
to Kurosaki as an S for the NCD.

137
00:11:30,022 --> 00:11:34,652
So you'll let the NCD do all the work,
then swoop in to steal the credit?

138
00:11:34,735 --> 00:11:35,694
Not quite.

139
00:11:35,778 --> 00:11:38,072
We'll utilize the NCD
to the fullest extent,

140
00:11:38,155 --> 00:11:39,698
and arrest the culprits at the end.

141
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,200
Same difference.

142
00:11:41,283 --> 00:11:44,662
In other words,
fatten the pigs before you slaughter them.

143
00:11:46,539 --> 00:11:48,416
Should a cop be saying that?

144
00:11:48,499 --> 00:11:49,417
Right.

145
00:11:51,085 --> 00:11:52,169
One more thing.

146
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:53,254
What?

147
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:57,550
What are these?

148
00:11:57,633 --> 00:11:59,802
I want you to infiltrate the Saeki Family.

149
00:12:00,469 --> 00:12:01,345
What?!

150
00:12:01,429 --> 00:12:03,514
Get your hands on their goods
and collect evidence.

151
00:12:03,597 --> 00:12:05,433
No, why me?

152
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:08,644
Infiltrate the yakuza?
Hell no. That's crazy dangerous.

153
00:12:08,727 --> 00:12:09,979
You don't get to refuse.

154
00:12:10,062 --> 00:12:11,355
First off,

155
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:15,359
they wouldn't let a nobody like me
have access to their precious merchandise.

156
00:12:16,569 --> 00:12:18,070
Don't you worry.

157
00:12:18,154 --> 00:12:20,948
The police will apply
some pressure to help you out.

158
00:12:46,432 --> 00:12:48,476
What the hell? Who?

159
00:12:52,938 --> 00:12:54,523
Long time no see.

160
00:13:01,238 --> 00:13:03,240
You little shit.

161
00:13:04,408 --> 00:13:06,410
You can't meet your damn quota.

162
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,582
You don't bother to keep in touch.

163
00:13:13,042 --> 00:13:17,087
I may be the merciful kind,
but even I have a fucking limit!

164
00:13:22,426 --> 00:13:24,220
Sorry, I had some things to deal with.

165
00:13:24,303 --> 00:13:27,181
I don't give a flying fuck
about your circumstances!

166
00:13:27,264 --> 00:13:28,307
I'll kill your ass.

167
00:13:30,559 --> 00:13:31,435
I'm sorry.

168
00:13:32,228 --> 00:13:33,479
I'll get the money.

169
00:13:34,063 --> 00:13:37,107
Then prepare ten million,
interest included.

170
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:40,486
-Ten million?
-Damn right. You're way past the deadline.

171
00:13:40,569 --> 00:13:41,820
But ten million is just--

172
00:13:41,904 --> 00:13:43,113
Too much?

173
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:44,782
Then here's an idea.

174
00:13:48,869 --> 00:13:50,579
How about we go for an eyeball?

175
00:13:50,663 --> 00:13:52,331
Please wait!

176
00:13:52,414 --> 00:13:54,625
You can get 500k for each one.

177
00:13:54,708 --> 00:13:56,835
I'll prepare the money ASAP.

178
00:13:58,295 --> 00:14:01,048
You think I'm going to trust that?

179
00:14:02,508 --> 00:14:03,342
Don't!

180
00:14:06,637 --> 00:14:07,513
Wait.

181
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:09,098
What?

182
00:14:10,474 --> 00:14:12,059
That's right.

183
00:14:12,142 --> 00:14:13,644
I almost forgot.

184
00:14:14,979 --> 00:14:16,105
Sorry?

185
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:20,484
The Saeki Family that has been looking
after us needs some more manpower.

186
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:22,945
You.

187
00:14:23,487 --> 00:14:25,030
Go help them for a few days.

188
00:14:25,114 --> 00:14:27,074
What? Why me?

189
00:14:27,157 --> 00:14:30,369
Fuck if I know! It's orders from above!

190
00:14:31,203 --> 00:14:33,372
Or would you rather offer the eyeballs?

191
00:14:33,914 --> 00:14:34,999
I'll go.

192
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:36,750
Seriously…

193
00:14:37,751 --> 00:14:40,713
We got ordered to give up
our meth rights unilaterally,

194
00:14:40,796 --> 00:14:42,673
which is a real fucking bummer.

195
00:14:42,756 --> 00:14:43,966
Don't you worry.

196
00:14:44,508 --> 00:14:47,303
The police will apply
some pressure to help you out.

197
00:14:48,721 --> 00:14:50,764
They don't seem to like it either.

198
00:14:52,099 --> 00:14:54,018
Who's gaining anything from it?

199
00:15:05,321 --> 00:15:06,989
Mr. Matsubara sent me.

200
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:08,365
I'm Umezawa.

201
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:09,450
Nice to meet you.

202
00:15:15,956 --> 00:15:17,583
Wipe your soles with this.

203
00:15:17,666 --> 00:15:18,584
What?

204
00:15:19,084 --> 00:15:19,960
Yes, sir.

205
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:22,755
I hear you're a dealer?

206
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:23,839
Yes, sir.

207
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,633
Give us your client list.

208
00:15:25,716 --> 00:15:28,135
-What?
-A list of your online customers!

209
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:30,137
-Yes, sir.
-Hurry it up.

210
00:15:30,763 --> 00:15:32,389
Let's see. Here it is.

211
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:36,977
What?

212
00:15:37,061 --> 00:15:38,479
Only 60 people?

213
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:42,316
Yes, I mostly sold in person.

214
00:15:44,401 --> 00:15:45,486
I guess it'll do.

215
00:15:46,070 --> 00:15:48,322
Refer those customers to us from now on.

216
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:51,283
What? But that's…

217
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:53,494
Got a problem with that?

218
00:15:56,580 --> 00:15:57,539
None.

219
00:15:58,248 --> 00:16:00,584
So, what will I be doing?

220
00:16:02,044 --> 00:16:03,879
Think about that yourself.

221
00:16:04,505 --> 00:16:05,339
Hello, sir.

222
00:16:05,422 --> 00:16:06,590
Hello, sir.

223
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:12,429
If you can't think for yourself,
stick to wiping the floors.

224
00:16:13,305 --> 00:16:14,181
Wiping the floors?

225
00:16:14,807 --> 00:16:16,058
What? You don't like it?

226
00:16:16,642 --> 00:16:17,559
No, sir.

227
00:16:18,602 --> 00:16:19,645
Listen up.

228
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:23,065
One look at how they clean
and I can tell if they're useful.

229
00:16:23,148 --> 00:16:25,734
If they seem trustworthy,
they'll get the goods.

230
00:16:25,818 --> 00:16:27,861
Shouldn't be a bad deal.

231
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:28,779
Yes, sir.

232
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:34,201
Hey. Who wiped the table today?

233
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:37,162
Sorry, I was still in the middle of it.

234
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:38,747
No excuses!

235
00:16:39,248 --> 00:16:40,582
I'm sorry, sir.

236
00:16:43,711 --> 00:16:45,379
Hey. What's this?

237
00:16:45,462 --> 00:16:46,922
Sir, that was me.

238
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:48,507
You got fingerprints on it!

239
00:16:49,717 --> 00:16:50,592
Sorry, sir.

240
00:16:50,676 --> 00:16:51,635
Hey.

241
00:16:52,845 --> 00:16:53,804
Like I always say,

242
00:16:54,722 --> 00:16:56,432
a dirty room equals a careless mind.

243
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:57,975
Every little bit adds up.

244
00:16:58,559 --> 00:17:00,144
A small error could prove fatal.

245
00:17:00,227 --> 00:17:01,729
Do it properly.

246
00:17:01,812 --> 00:17:02,855
Right, Shinichi?

247
00:17:03,439 --> 00:17:04,314
I'm Shinji, sir.

248
00:17:04,398 --> 00:17:06,400
Does it fucking matter?

249
00:17:07,151 --> 00:17:09,528
-I'm Shinichi--
-You too!

250
00:17:13,782 --> 00:17:16,243
The guy is an actual psycho.

251
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:18,579
A clean freak yakuza? Give me a break.

252
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:21,206
It's not a joke!

253
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:24,001
Well, at least the infiltration went well.

254
00:17:25,127 --> 00:17:27,463
All thanks to the pressure
you guys applied.

255
00:17:27,546 --> 00:17:30,883
They've got their backers too.
The higher-ups are all connected.

256
00:17:31,508 --> 00:17:33,677
Police, yakuza. Is there a difference?

257
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:37,473
Next, you have to make Kurosaki
accept this plan.

258
00:17:37,973 --> 00:17:41,226
Crushing a trafficking operation
should be tempting to him.

259
00:17:41,310 --> 00:17:43,479
Right, I still have to do that.

260
00:17:43,562 --> 00:17:47,441
Just so we're clear,
if Kurosaki catches on to this plan,

261
00:17:47,983 --> 00:17:49,860
you will stop being an S for the NCD

262
00:17:49,943 --> 00:17:52,821
and become a roach
harmful to their investigation.

263
00:17:53,655 --> 00:17:56,158
That is to say,
a traitor to be disposed of.

264
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:58,827
By dispose, you mean they'll arrest me?

265
00:17:58,911 --> 00:18:01,455
Would be nice if that's all it was.

266
00:18:01,538 --> 00:18:03,582
Wait, you'll help if it gets bad, right?

267
00:18:03,665 --> 00:18:06,126
You will also lose value
as an S for the police.

268
00:18:06,210 --> 00:18:07,961
You'll have to wipe your own ass.

269
00:18:08,045 --> 00:18:09,171
You can't be serious!

270
00:18:09,254 --> 00:18:10,964
To avoid that,

271
00:18:11,715 --> 00:18:14,802
take the utmost care
not to let Kurosaki catch on to us.

272
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:20,390
His instinct on drug-related matters
is monstrously accurate, after all.

273
00:18:22,392 --> 00:18:23,769
Damn.

274
00:18:44,289 --> 00:18:46,750
Can you not brew coffee in my house?

275
00:18:48,627 --> 00:18:51,171
What did you want to discuss? Get to it.

276
00:18:53,632 --> 00:18:54,800
Yes, well,

277
00:18:55,425 --> 00:18:58,137
you remember the talk
about adding a new cocaine route

278
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:00,305
to people connected to Nagata?

279
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:01,557
Yes.

280
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,100
How about we don't do that?

281
00:19:03,851 --> 00:19:06,270
What? Insubordination? I'll arrest you.

282
00:19:06,353 --> 00:19:07,855
Come on, just listen.

283
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:12,276
If we follow your plan,
it puts me in a really bad position.

284
00:19:12,359 --> 00:19:15,737
I could die if the traffickers
set their sights on me.

285
00:19:15,821 --> 00:19:17,656
Endeavor not to die. Request denied.

286
00:19:17,739 --> 00:19:18,782
Let me finish.

287
00:19:18,866 --> 00:19:19,950
Go on.

288
00:19:21,785 --> 00:19:22,828
Right.

289
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:27,166
Catching the guys selling to Nagata
would be nice and all,

290
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:31,545
but wouldn't it be even better to catch
the underlying organization behind it all?

291
00:19:31,628 --> 00:19:34,590
And how would we investigate
the said organization?

292
00:19:34,673 --> 00:19:37,259
The NCD is still working
to pin them down right now.

293
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:46,226
The Saeki Family.

294
00:19:47,519 --> 00:19:50,439
Why would an underling like you know that?

295
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:53,066
Even as an underling,

296
00:19:53,150 --> 00:19:55,986
once I knew that it was Nagata
giving Kaga cocaine,

297
00:19:56,528 --> 00:19:58,655
I had enough intel to piece it together.

298
00:20:00,324 --> 00:20:02,993
-Is that intel reliable?
-I promise you, it is.

299
00:20:04,119 --> 00:20:06,163
I already started tracking their trail.

300
00:20:10,125 --> 00:20:12,753
Unusually efficient and proactive of you.

301
00:20:13,253 --> 00:20:14,546
Is there a catch?

302
00:20:17,424 --> 00:20:20,636
I just want to raise my chances
of survival any way I can.

303
00:20:22,763 --> 00:20:25,849
We've had the Saeki Family
marked for some time now,

304
00:20:25,933 --> 00:20:27,768
but never had conclusive evidence.

305
00:20:29,061 --> 00:20:31,271
The NCD can do sting operations, right?

306
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:35,067
In that case,
I'll infiltrate the smuggling operation.

307
00:20:36,652 --> 00:20:37,486
What?

308
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:38,695
In other words,

309
00:20:41,323 --> 00:20:43,450
we fatten the pigs for the slaughter.

310
00:20:46,161 --> 00:20:47,537
Think about it.

311
00:20:48,163 --> 00:20:51,708
If I infiltrate it, we can grasp
the entire flow of the cocaine.

312
00:20:52,542 --> 00:20:53,585
With this plan,

313
00:20:53,669 --> 00:20:58,215
we can get more than just the people
who directly sold the cocaine to Nagata.

314
00:21:00,092 --> 00:21:02,678
I don't know what you're scheming…

315
00:21:04,471 --> 00:21:06,765
but I'm intrigued. I'm in.

316
00:21:06,848 --> 00:21:08,433
Okay, then let's be quick--

317
00:21:08,517 --> 00:21:09,518
That said,

318
00:21:09,601 --> 00:21:13,021
if you're infiltrating, you need
to bring back some evidence.

319
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:14,231
Evidence?

320
00:21:14,314 --> 00:21:15,190
Yes.

321
00:21:15,857 --> 00:21:18,986
Information about big deals
or their smuggling routes.

322
00:21:19,069 --> 00:21:20,320
The client list.

323
00:21:20,821 --> 00:21:22,364
Where would I…

324
00:21:22,990 --> 00:21:25,742
Search for it. Find it. Bring it.
That's my condition.

325
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:29,371
All right.

326
00:21:31,999 --> 00:21:32,833
Umezawa.

327
00:21:32,916 --> 00:21:33,875
What?

328
00:21:35,544 --> 00:21:36,378
Take this.

329
00:21:37,629 --> 00:21:39,172
What's this, all of a sudden?

330
00:21:39,256 --> 00:21:40,465
A good luck charm.

331
00:21:41,133 --> 00:21:43,427
What gives? You're creeping me out.

332
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:46,596
You'll have to protect yourself.

333
00:21:46,680 --> 00:21:48,682
You weren't trying to be nice?

334
00:21:50,017 --> 00:21:50,976
Wait.

335
00:21:52,144 --> 00:21:53,603
Your legs fall asleep?

336
00:21:53,687 --> 00:21:54,938
No, they did not.

337
00:21:57,274 --> 00:21:58,191
There.

338
00:21:58,984 --> 00:21:59,943
Take that.

339
00:22:01,653 --> 00:22:03,572
-Here.
-Stop. I'll arrest you.

340
00:22:03,655 --> 00:22:06,950
Try it. Come on. Come at me.

341
00:22:07,576 --> 00:22:09,703
Just try it. Come on.

342
00:22:09,786 --> 00:22:12,748
Over here. Try and get me.

343
00:22:27,721 --> 00:22:28,972
Hello, sir!

344
00:22:29,681 --> 00:22:31,183
Where's Shinichi and Shinji?

345
00:22:31,266 --> 00:22:32,809
They went to buy drinks.

346
00:22:32,893 --> 00:22:34,811
They left a newbie alone?

347
00:22:44,946 --> 00:22:46,448
Did you wipe all of this?

348
00:22:46,531 --> 00:22:48,492
Sorry, it was me.

349
00:22:51,328 --> 00:22:52,454
You pass.

350
00:22:53,538 --> 00:22:54,414
What?

351
00:22:54,498 --> 00:22:56,625
Nice and thorough work.

352
00:22:57,667 --> 00:22:59,127
Thank you, sir.

353
00:22:59,211 --> 00:23:00,921
All right then.

354
00:23:01,004 --> 00:23:04,216
Go to the dock right now
and collect our monthly shipment.

355
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:06,635
What kind of shipment?

356
00:23:08,553 --> 00:23:09,805
Cocaine.

357
00:23:11,556 --> 00:23:13,683
Someone else will handle the payment.

358
00:23:13,767 --> 00:23:16,728
You just get the shipment
and contact me immediately.

359
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:18,230
Ask Shinichi the details.

360
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:19,815
Yes, sir.

361
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:26,988
That's mission accomplished.

362
00:23:27,572 --> 00:23:28,740
Great job.

363
00:23:28,824 --> 00:23:30,742
<i>Want to try dying once?</i>

364
00:23:30,826 --> 00:23:31,952
<i>Who the hell are you?</i>

365
00:23:32,536 --> 00:23:33,620
Hey!

366
00:23:33,703 --> 00:23:35,747
KUROSAKI RUSHES IN TO SAVE UMEZAWA?

367
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:37,124
Don't move!

368
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:38,083
Or he dies.

369
00:23:38,166 --> 00:23:40,460
<i>But killing a narcotics agent…</i>

370
00:23:40,544 --> 00:23:42,129
<i>What other choice is there?</i>

371
00:23:43,630 --> 00:23:44,923
<i>How many will die?</i>

372
00:23:45,006 --> 00:23:48,385
If their numbers are in both
of your phones, I'll trust you.

373
00:23:48,468 --> 00:23:49,594
However,

374
00:23:49,678 --> 00:23:51,888
if they aren't…

375
00:23:52,889 --> 00:23:54,391
it's over for you.

376
00:23:55,016 --> 00:24:00,939
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS,
GROUPS, OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

377
00:24:01,022 --> 00:24:01,982
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan
